@startuml Signup Flows - API Sequence Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 20
skinparam maxmessagesize 60

title TWS ERP - Signup Flow API Sequence (User Perspective)

actor User as U
participant "Landing Page" as LP
participant "Signup Modal" as SM
participant "Email Validation API" as EVA
participant "Signup API" as SA
participant "Email Service" as ES
participant "Tenant API" as TA
participant "Provisioning Service" as PS

== Step 1: Account Creation ==

U -> LP: Click "Start Free Trial"
LP -> SM: Open signup modal (detect industry)
SM -> SM: Load industry-specific flow

U -> SM: Fill registration form
SM -> SM: Validate form fields
SM -> SM: Validate password strength

U -> SM: Enter email
SM -> EVA: GET /api/email/validate?email=...
EVA -> EVA: Check format
EVA -> EVA: Check disposable domains
EVA -> EVA: Check MX records
EVA --> SM: {valid: true/false, message: "..."}

alt Email invalid
    SM --> U: Show error message
    U -> SM: Correct email
else Email valid
    U -> SM: Submit form
    SM -> SA: POST /api/signup/register\n{email, password, fullName, industry}
    
    SA -> SA: Validate email format
    SA -> SA: Check email exists
    SA -> SA: Validate password strength
    SA -> SA: Hash password (bcrypt)
    SA -> SA: Create user account
    SA -> SA: Generate 6-digit OTP
    SA -> SA: Create email verification record
    SA -> ES: Send verification email (OTP)
    ES -> ES: Queue email job
    ES --> SA: Email queued
    SA --> SM: {success: true, userId, verificationId}
    
    SM -> SM: Store userId, verificationId
    SM -> SM: Navigate to Step 2
    SM --> U: Show email verification screen
end

== Step 2: Email Verification ==

U -> SM: Enter 6-digit OTP
U -> SM: Submit OTP

SM -> SA: POST /api/signup/verify-email\n{email, otp}

SA -> SA: Find verification record
SA -> SA: Check OTP matches
SA -> SA: Check OTP not expired
SA -> SA: Mark email as verified
SA -> SA: Update user.emailVerified = true
SA --> SM: {success: true, userId}

alt OTP invalid or expired
    SA --> SM: {success: false, message: "Invalid OTP"}
    SM --> U: Show error message
    U -> SM: Click "Resend OTP"
    SM -> SA: POST /api/signup/resend-otp\n{email}
    SA -> SA: Generate new OTP
    SA -> ES: Send new verification email
    ES --> SA: Email queued
    SA --> SM: {success: true, message: "Code resent"}
    SM --> U: Show "Code resent" message
else OTP valid
    SM -> SM: Navigate to Step 3
    SM --> U: Show industry-specific form
end

== Step 3: Industry-Specific Information ==

U -> SM: Fill industry-specific fields
note right of SM
  Education: schoolName, schoolType, etc.
  Healthcare: facilityName, facilityType, etc.
  Software House: companyName, teamSize, etc.
  Warehouse: warehouseName, warehouseType, etc.
  Business: organizationName
end note

U -> SM: Enter tenant subdomain (slug)
SM -> SM: Validate slug format (3-50 chars, lowercase, numbers, hyphens)

SM -> TA: GET /api/signup/check-slug-availability?slug=...
TA -> TA: Check slug format
TA -> TA: Query database for existing slug
TA --> SM: {success: true, available: true/false, message: "..."}

alt Slug not available
    SM --> U: Show "Not available" error
    U -> SM: Enter different slug
    SM -> TA: GET /api/signup/check-slug-availability?slug=...
    TA --> SM: Check availability
else Slug available
    SM --> U: Show "✓ Available" status
    U -> SM: Submit form
    SM -> SM: Navigate to Step 4 (or confirmation for Business)
end

== Step 4: Tenant Creation ==

U -> SM: Submit tenant creation form
SM -> TA: POST /api/signup/create-tenant\n{userId, industry, organizationName, slug, metadata}

TA -> TA: Validate slug availability (double-check)
TA -> TA: Create tenant record
TA -> TA: Assign user as tenant admin (TenantRole)
TA -> TA: Apply industry-specific template
TA -> TA: Create onboarding checklist
TA -> PS: Trigger tenant provisioning job
note right of PS
  Async provisioning:
  - Database setup
  - Default configurations
  - Industry-specific data
  - Welcome email
end note
PS -> PS: Queue provisioning job (BullMQ)
PS --> TA: Job queued
TA -> ES: Send tenant welcome email
ES --> TA: Email queued
TA --> SM: {success: true, tenant: {...}}

alt Tenant creation failed
    TA --> SM: {success: false, message: "..."}
    SM --> U: Show error message
else Tenant created successfully
    SM -> SM: Navigate to confirmation step
    SM --> U: Show "Welcome! Your [Industry] ERP is being set up"
    
    note right of SM
      Confirmation screen shows:
      - Success message
      - Progress indicator
      - Estimated setup time
    end note
    
    SM -> SM: Wait 3 seconds
    SM -> SM: Redirect to tenant subdomain
    SM --> U: Navigate to https://[slug].tws.example.com/onboarding
end

== Post-Signup (Background) ==

PS -> PS: Execute provisioning job
PS -> PS: Set up tenant database
PS -> PS: Apply industry template
PS -> PS: Configure default settings
PS -> PS: Create initial data
PS -> PS: Mark tenant as active
PS -> ES: Send welcome email with login details
ES --> U: Welcome email delivered

U -> U: Access tenant subdomain
U -> U: Complete onboarding checklist
U -> U: Start using ERP

@enduml
